imagine an attacker steals a database of 1,000,000 users, and they guess that many people are using the password password123.
Without a Salt: The attacker hashes password123 one time. They then check that single output against all 1,000,000 stolen hashes. If 5,000 users used that password, the attacker just cracked 5,000 accounts with a single calculation.
